If this posts, don't be fooled by the star rating - only reviews 3 stars and above automatically post. Ratings anywhere below are censored and never posted. Here is my full review - I have since stayed away from Foodpanda because of its interests in protecting their partners over being honest to enhance the experience of their customers by filtering out reviews with poor ratings. 

Under no circumstances order the "Norwegian shrimp" on "brioche", which is a euphemism for four frozen shrimp with itty bits of capsicum on a slice of bread for $10. Same goes for the 'mash garlic potato' side with the steak(s), which is a small dry scoop of suspiciously potato-flakey reconstituted mash. Don't bother with the chimichurri sauce, it's over-oiled and the herbs taste stale. 

The fries side is acceptable (in relation) and the steak was done to request but frankly mediocre and not worth the money. For $20, you can get a really lovely cut of steak and panfry it with more flavour than Cafe Etc could ever give you. 

Delivery time was the only upside, but I suspect it's because Cafe Etc wasn't in charge of that.

If this posts, don't be fooled by the star rating - only reviews 3 stars and above automatically post. Ratings anywhere below are censored and never posted. Here is my full review - I have since stayed away from Foodpanda because of its interests in protecting their partners over being honest to enhance the experience of their customers by filtering out reviews with poor ratings. 

Under no circumstances order the "Norwegian shrimp" on "brioche", which is a euphemism for four frozen shrimp with itty bits of capsicum on a slice of bread for $10. Same goes for the 'mash garlic potato' side with the steak(s), which is a small dry scoop of suspiciously potato-flakey reconstituted mash. Don't bother with the chimichurri sauce, it's over-oiled and the herbs taste stale. 

The fries side is acceptable (in relation) and the steak was done to request but frankly mediocre and not worth the money. For $20, you can get a really lovely cut of steak and panfry it with more flavour than Cafe Etc could ever give you. 

Delivery time was the only upside, but I suspect it's because Cafe Etc wasn't in charge of that.

Caesar salad was really nice and smoothie was great. Tiramisu was delicious with real cream.

All in all great experience.

reviews.description: I mentioned for vegetarian I found chicken

We ordered ‚ÄúNasi Goreng with butter chicken‚Äù. Butter chicken- ah yes the slightly sweet, mildly spiced soft chicken, cooked and served in a generous amount of tangy tomato sauce. What we got? Fried rice with chicken cooked in butter. As in, plain white chicken in plain white butter. What Singaporean would ever expect that? From a place that also serves murtabak, Prata and other Indian dishes no less.

That aside, if we were to put aside our disappointment and review the dish for what it (sadly) was, it was still not fantastic. While the fried rice portion was fairly tasty at first, there was too much loose butter which made the rice below quite mushy! The chicken was... fine. But definitely NOT worth $9.10. Neither one of us finished our food despite being very hungry.

Hi, foodpanda. Since this is an email dedicated to reporting an issue with a rider, I'll give a detailed explanation of what happened, so as to prevent misunderstandings on both our parts. Firstly, the food came half an hour late. I have no issues on that, since the restaurant could have been having more customers at that time. Completely not your fault. Then, another issue popped up. The rider. I expected my food to arrive when the rider had said that he had arrived, but well, clearly I was wrong. The rider claimed to be at my floor, at my block, in my condominium. He wasn't. He insisted he was at block 52 (the block I stay at), and when i told him I could not see anyone outside my door, he insisted he was at my place. He went down to my basement, up to the 28th floor again, insisting over and over again he was at my block. I then asked for a picture of his surroundings, so I could confirm that he was indeed at my place. He did not reply. Ok, so what do I do now? I called him. I asked him where he was, trying to find out where he could be, since he definitely wasn't at my place. He went mumbling abit, going all "uhh" and such. He then suddenly asked me where I stayed. Really? I was quite sure I had keyed in my address when I ordered my food. Fine. I told him the name of the condominium I stay at, before he suddenly realised he was at the WRONG condominium. Not the wrong block, nor the wrong floor. But the WRONG condominium? How clueless does one have to be to mess that up? Sure, everyone makes mistakes. But his insistent attitude, and nonchalant behaviour as if he did not care that he could have made a mistake is why I am writing this email. If he spoke with more sincerity, maybe even slightly apologetically, I wouldn't be writing this email. I'm not sure how you guys hire riders, but I sure would like you guys to reconsider how you hire your riders. 
Now, I'm sitting on my chair, furiously typing out this email. In front of me is my meal that I paid 13 dollars for: a crushed up box of my meal, soggy fries, and the fact that this whole experience left a bad taste in my mouth. Guess that counts as a free of charge dish. Thanks.
